I got really sick when I was like two, and it was requested that I have a surgery to correct something with my bladder, and so they went in and fixed it. And I had been in and out of doctors offices, in emergency rooms or whatnot, and no doctor would even tell me what was going on with me until last year when I went to a new doctor and they did this scan and test on me and they told me what had happened. And then I had to go in and literally have a whole thing of pee drained out of me. So this last year was like the first year Ive actually been healthy in so many years. So I have not really been able to hold a job over these last so many years other than doing volunteer work and such. But I had some situations happen to myself in my school years or whatever, and I never knew that it could happen to other people. And so as I got older I dont like to say that Im old or anything, but when I was going to school, we didnt have computers to this magnitude of cell phones and all that. And so this is a whole new field for a lot of people that dont understand whats going on. But as Im myself trying to get older, growing up, getting older and stuff, about ten years ago, I got my first smartphone and somebody suggested to me to put an app on my phone and theyre like, oh yeah, its a lot of fun. You can go on this app and see a lot of things and meet a lot of new people and whatever. And I didnt really think anything of it. I just put the app on my phone and kind of started looking around and it was pretty fun at first because I could see like, the state of Florida, disney World and the London Bridge, and then I can stuff all over the country, all over the world, basically. But then I started seeing all these kids on this app too. And not only were kids on this app, but they were just offered. Offered is not the correct word, but the app basically was where people can go and meet people online and talk to strangers. These kids were going online and talking with people that they dont even know who they are, and sometimes they were in their homes and sometimes they were at school, but there were so many different times in those conversations that kids were telling the people where they lived. Older teenagers were telling them how many people about their personal lives, which they had no business sharing to begin with, sort of like grooming kind of stuff. And so one time I found this girl on this app and she lived 40 minutes from where I live, and by clicking on her profile, I was able to click on the link and it basically told me the locations where she was at. And I found the school where she was going to. I quickly just Googled the school and found a phone number. And I called the school to tell the principal, hey, one of your students is talking inappropriately to two men in a classroom right now. And so in a conversation in the hallway, he says to the girl, hey, someone called the school about you. Maybe you shouldnt be on that app. So she stayed off of it for like two days, but then she went right back onto it. So when I called the school back to say, hey, look, shes back on this app or whatever, they basically said to me, well, they talked to the parents before about her Internet usage. Were just not going to get involved this time.
And so I want to get out in front of all that and teach them about Internet safety and stuff like that. Keeping them educated on the positive road.
